Got this game while looking for some cool co-op games and it was on sale. One of the best impulse acquisitions I've made on Steam so far.

Pros:

+ Cool graphics;
+ Excellent soundtrack ;
+ Great gameplay;
+ Despite having only 5 characters, the combinations of primary and secondary weapons, plus the unique traits of each robot, give us some nice diversity;
+ Campaign stages are well-made enough, but Challenge mode is amazing and very, very fun;
+ Clever and challenging, but nowhere near impossible, achievements
+ Gamepad support.

Cons:

- Lack of online co-op (According to the developer itself, no chances of having this feature in the future; demands a big rewrite and, thus, many resources);
- Occasional FPS drops, but nothing a mid-tier computer can't handle;
- Lack of mech customization features (A personal pet peeve, not a big con itself)

Summary: Great shmup title, enough to keep entertained for dozens of hours, and a fun title to playing with your friends. Get it.
